c conventions 

1.function documantation in header file-

/*

	Describing the function
	Input - paramenters to the function
	Output - function output
*/
void function()

2.function name convention -

lower case separated by underscore
void some_function()

3.local variable name convention- 
lower case separated by underscore

int some_variable;

4. global variable name convention-

start with g_ resumed by lower case separated by underscore

int g_some_global_variable;